cook <b>5 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>."},{"content":"Place Varoma dish into position and place spiralised carrot and parsnip into it. Secure Varoma lid and steam <b>5 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>. Remove Varoma and set aside."},{"content":"Add lima beans, salt and pepper into mixing bowl. Place Varoma dish into position and add zucchini into it, then cook <b>8 min\/100°C\/\/speed <b>. Transfer vegetables in Varoma into a large bowl and set aside."},{"content":"Add lemon juice, coriander and dill and heat <b>2 min\/100°C\/\/speed <b>. Divide between 4 serving bowls and garnish with spiralised vegetables before serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Please refer to <em>The Basic Cookbook <\/em>or <em>Everyday Cookbook <\/em>for the Vegetable stock paste recipe.","Spiralizers are available to buy from most home and kitchen shops. These can be used to shred a range of vegetables into ribbons. This is a fun and appealing way to add vegetables to your dish. You can also use a julienne peeler."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","9h","4 portions"]}